  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Key legal elements typically include:\n\n1. Basic legal definition:\n- Concealing the origin of money obtained from criminal activities\n- Transforming illegal funds into seemingly legitimate income\n- Disguising the source of illicitly gained money\n\n2. Common legal elements:\n- Intentional financial transactions\n- Knowing the funds originated from illegal activities\n- Attempting to hide or disguise the funds' criminal source\n- Conducting transactions to promote illegal activities\n\n3. Typical stages of money laundering:\n- Placement: Introducing illegal funds into financial system\n- Layering: Conducting complex financial transactions\n- Integration: Making funds appear legitimate\n\n4. Jurisdictional variations:\n- Different countries have specific legal definitions\n- Specific criminal statutes vary by region\n- Penalties and prosecution standards differ\n\n5. Regulated financial activities:\n- Banks must report suspicious transactions\n- Financial institutions required to perform due diligence\n- Mandatory reporting of large cash transactions\n\nPlease note this is general legal information and not specific legal advice. Consult a legal professional for precise guidance.",
